---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Sidebar from '../../components/Sidebar.astro';
const title = "H I 21-cm Line Observations - ArXiv Atlas";

import WikiLink from '../../components/WikiLink.astro';
---
<Base title={title}>
  <Sidebar />
  <main class="page-main">
    <h1 class="page-title">H I 21-cm Line Observations</h1>

    <p>The H I 21-cm line (rest 1.420 GHz) is the primary tracer of neutral atomic hydrogen in galaxies. Imaging and spectroscopy of the 21-cm line provide gas masses, rotation curves, kinematics, and environmental maps (e.g., group members, tidal features).</p>

    <h2 id="section-0">Techniques & Facilities</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Interferometry: VLA, MeerKAT, ASKAP — spatially resolved H I cubes and kinematics.</li>
      <li>Single-dish: FAST, Arecibo (legacy) — sensitive wide-area H I surveys.</li>
      <li>Analysis tools: SoFiA, BBarolo for source finding and 3D kinematic modelling.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="section-1">Observational Diagnostics</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Double-horn profiles indicate rotation-dominated disks.</li>
      <li>Asymmetric wings and extended low-surface-brightness H I trace tidal interactions and gas accretion.</li>
      <li>Nuclear H I absorption can indicate cold gas in front of compact continuum sources.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="section-2">Examples</h2>
    <p>Feng et al. (2026) use VLA + FAST H I imaging to show IRAS 04296+2923 resides in a small group, with rotation-dominated H I kinematics and a compact nuclear starburst in the primary galaxy<sup>[1]</sup>.</p>

    <h2 id="section-3">References</h2>
    <ol>
      <li id="ref1">Feng, G., Wu, Z., Zhang, C., Zhu, M. (2026). "H I 21-cm Line Properties of the Nearby LIRG IRAS 04296+2923." arXiv:2603.11899.</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="page-tags">
      <strong>Tags:</strong>
      <WikiLink slug="pages/Tag_HI" text="H I" />
      <WikiLink slug="pages/Tag_Radio_Astronomy" text="Radio Astronomy" />
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
